The paper deals with the use of machine learning models (neural networks and gradient boosting models) to approximate outcomes of traffic simulations for traffic optimization tasks. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of genetic algorithms for optimization, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with real-time traffic optimization, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
